text: Mississippi County is a county of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 40,685. There are two county seats, Blytheville and Osceola. The county was founded on November 1, 1833, and named for the Mississippi River which borders the county to the east. == References == Category:1833 establishments in Arkansas Territory Category:Arkansas counties
title: Mississippi County, Arkansas
